+# International rollout — manageable segments
+
+## Segment A (completed in this commit)
+- [x] Create language roots for `en`, `zh-cn`, `tr`, `ru`.
+- [x] Add localized core pages for each language:
+  - home
+  - services
+  - about
+  - contact
+  - jobs
+  - blog
+- [x] Add language switcher on every new core page.
+- [x] Add canonical + hreflang on every new core page.
+- [x] Extend root redirect pages (`/` and `/sr-me/`) with multilingual hreflang set.
+
+## Segment B (next)
+- [x] Map and create service detail pages per language.
+- [x] Ensure internal links from each localized services index point to detail pages.
+- [x] Add localized meta descriptions per service detail page.
+
+## Segment C (next)
+- [x] Create localized blog post structure (first batch p01–p10 across 4 languages).
+- [x] Add reciprocal language links between equivalent posts.
+- [x] Validate no broken internal links.
+
+## Segment D (next)
+- [x] Create remaining blog batches (p11–p30).
+- [x] Update sitemap generation output to include all newly indexable language URLs.
+- [x] Re-run SEO + link QA reports and resolve gaps.
+
+## Segment E (final)
+- [x] Content polish pass (tone consistency, CTA consistency, legal wording).
+- [x] Final QA report with URL counts by language and ready-to-merge checklist.
